
Overview of noun gauntlet

The noun gauntlet has 4 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                     
1. gauntlet, gantlet -- (to offer or accept a challenge; "threw down the gauntlet"; "took up the gauntlet")
2. gauntlet, gantlet, metal glove -- (a glove of armored leather; protects the hand)
3. gauntlet, gantlet -- (a glove with long sleeve)
4. gauntlet, gantlet -- (a form of punishment in which a person is forced to run between two lines of men facing each other and armed with clubs or whips to beat the victim)
